This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the key technology for machine learning problem, which is Automl. Additionally, it proposes a method to accelerate traditional hyperparameter optimization methods, which is a common problem in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses the use of machine learning models and gradient information to optimize hyperparameters. 

Furthermore, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as hyperparameter optimization is a crucial step in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. 

It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper discusses the optimization of hyperparameters, which is a common problem in neural networks. 

Lastly, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper proposes a method to optimize hyperparameters, which is a crucial step in building control systems.
